<title type="html"><![CDATA[No background in Link's Awakening]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3637&amp;p=27638#p27638"><![CDATA[
The game probably doesn't fully validate the save game data. It might claim to have 100 hearts and cause the heart-drawing routine to corrupt other things, or similar. This must have always been a worry on those battery-RAM cartridges, that the data would become corrupt in a way that rendered the cartridge unusable until it were physically opened and the battery removed for a while. I imagine checksums were there for this reason, rather than preventing cheating.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Sat Oct 13, 2007 4:12 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
